## Context

This is the OpenAI adapter for the ADK-Go agent system. The adapter implements `model.LLM` interface which has `GenerateContent(ctx, req, streaming) iter.Seq2[*model.LLMResponse, error]`. The adapter is called by ADK's runner multiple times during an agent run ŌĆö first for the initial prompt, then for tool call results, etc.

The key insight: ADK sends the full conversation history in `req.Contents` each time. For the Responses API, we need to convert:
- `model` role FunctionCall parts ŌåÆ `{type: "function_call"}` input items (echo)
- `model` role FunctionResponse parts ŌåÆ `{type: "function_call_output"}` input items
- text parts ŌåÆ `{type: "message"}` input items
- System instruction ŌåÆ separate `instructions` field

Note: `NewModel` gains a 4th parameter `wsConfig *WebSearch` ŌĆö this will temporarily break callers in `model.go` but that gets fixed in the next task. Just make the package compile on its own.

